The paper discusses the design of a cross-point architecture for STT-MRAM, which involves the integration of memory cells and transistors. This falls under the category of Emerging Technologies (cs.ET) as it deals with a new technology for memory storage. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of SPICE models and simulation techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of Architecture (cs.AR). The paper also addresses issues related to sneak currents and low-speed, which are relevant to the sub-categories of Neural Networks and Learning (cs.NE) and Electromagnetics (cs.EM), respectively. Finally, the paper presents chip characteristic results, which are relevant to the sub-category of Modeling and Simulation (cs.MS).
